# .env.example — Herald V3 quickstart credentials template.
#
# Copy this to the REPO ROOT as ".env" (which IS git-ignored per Universal
# Constitution §11.4.10) before running the quickstart compose. See
# docs/guides/OPERATOR_CREDENTIALS.md for the comprehensive step-by-step
# guide on obtaining each value.
#
# Resolution order (12-factor; spec V3 §3.3):
#
#   1. explicit CLI flag (highest precedence)
#   2. shell-exported env var (.bashrc / .zshrc / k8s ConfigMap / CI secret)
#   3. value from this .env (fallback only — DOES NOT override shell exports)
#   4. compiled default (lowest)
#
# Shell exports ALWAYS win over .env. This means an operator can have
# team defaults in .env while still overriding per-developer-host via
# .bashrc. Never paste real credentials into this file — every value
# below is a placeholder ("change-me-…", "xxxxx", "<example>").

# =====================================================================
# REQUIRED — Postgres (HRD-010 LIVE)
# =====================================================================
# Choose a strong random value: openssl rand -base64 32

HERALD_DB_HOST=127.0.0.1
HERALD_DB_PORT=24100
HERALD_DB_USER=herald
HERALD_DB_PASSWORD=change-me-strong-postgres-password
HERALD_DB_NAME=herald

# DSN form used by `pherald migrate` CLI. Set explicitly when the CLI
# is invoked from a context that doesn't carry the split HERALD_DB_*
# env vars. NOT auto-composed from the above.
HERALD_PG_DSN=postgres://herald:change-me-strong-postgres-password@127.0.0.1:24100/herald

# =====================================================================
# REQUIRED — Redis (HRD-010 LIVE)
# =====================================================================
# Choose a strong random value: openssl rand -base64 32

HERALD_REDIS_ADDR=127.0.0.1:24200
HERALD_REDIS_PASSWORD=change-me-strong-redis-password
HERALD_REDIS_DB=0

# =====================================================================
# REQUIRED for Telegram channel — HRD-011 (LIVE)
# =====================================================================
# Obtain via @BotFather in Telegram. See OPERATOR_CREDENTIALS.md
# §"Telegram" for step-by-step instructions.

# HERALD_TGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=1234567890:AAH-example-replace-with-your-real-token-here
# HERALD_TGRAM_CHAT_ID=-1001234567890

# Set to "1" to enable the E19 vertical-slice test's live-inbound path
# (operator hand-sends a Telegram message during the test window).
# Leave unset for everyday operation.
# HERALD_TGRAM_LIVE_INBOUND=

# Reserved for future webhook-ingress (HRD-NNN). 256-bit hex secret.
# Generate via: openssl rand -hex 32
# HERALD_TGRAM_WEBHOOK_SECRET=

# =====================================================================
# REQUIRED for Claude Code dispatcher — HRD-012 (LIVE)
# =====================================================================
# See OPERATOR_CREDENTIALS.md §"Claude Code dispatcher" for setup.

# Path to the `claude` CLI binary. If `claude` is on $PATH, leave unset.
HERALD_CLAUDE_BIN=claude

# Project name used to resolve the session anchor file (§33.2).
# MUST match a filename-safe identifier — typically your repo folder name.
HERALD_CLAUDE_PROJECT_NAME=Herald

# (Optional) Pre-existing Claude session UUID. If unset, Herald
# auto-bootstraps a new session on first Dispatch and persists the
# UUID to <workdir>/.herald/claude-code/sessions/<project>.session.
# HERALD_CLAUDE_SESSION_UUID=

# (Optional) Working dir for `claude --resume` cmd.Dir. Defaults to ".".
# HERALD_CLAUDE_WORKDIR=

# =====================================================================
# Tenant + project identity
# =====================================================================
# Default single-tenant UUID. Override per deploy.
HERALD_TENANT_ID=00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001
HERALD_PROJECT_NAME=Herald

# =====================================================================
# RESERVED — Slack channel (HRD-NNN, planned V2)
# =====================================================================
# Spec V3 §11.2. Env-var names stable; uncomment when Slack lands.

# HERALD_SLACK_BOT_TOKEN=xoxb-your-real-bot-token-here
# HERALD_SLACK_SIGNING_SECRET=your-signing-secret
# HERALD_SLACK_APP_TOKEN=xapp-your-real-app-token-here  # Socket Mode alt
# HERALD_SLACK_DEFAULT_CHANNEL=C012345ABCD

# =====================================================================
# RESERVED — Email (SMTP) channel (HRD-NNN, planned V2)
# =====================================================================
# Spec V3 §11.4.

# HERALD_SMTP_HOST=smtp.example.com
# HERALD_SMTP_PORT=587
# HERALD_SMTP_USERNAME=herald@example.com
# HERALD_SMTP_PASSWORD=change-me-strong-smtp-password
# HERALD_SMTP_FROM=herald@example.com

# =====================================================================
# RESERVED — Email (Resend) channel (HRD-NNN, planned V2)
# =====================================================================
# Alternative to raw SMTP. Spec V3 §11.4.

# HERALD_RESEND_API_KEY=re_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
# HERALD_RESEND_FROM=herald@example.com

# =====================================================================
# RESERVED — Max channel (HRD-NNN, planned V2)
# =====================================================================
# Russian-market messenger; Bot API similar to Telegram. Spec V3 §11.3.

# HERALD_MAX_BOT_TOKEN=
# HERALD_MAX_CHAT_ID=

# =====================================================================
# RESERVED — later-iteration channels
# =====================================================================
# Microsoft Teams (V3), Lark, Discord, WhatsApp, Viber — env-var names
# defined when each HRD opens. Reserved comment-block kept here so the
# operator's .env stays aligned with the spec's roadmap.

# HERALD_TEAMS_* / HERALD_LARK_* / HERALD_DISCORD_* / HERALD_WHATSAPP_*
# / HERALD_VIBER_* — see OPERATOR_CREDENTIALS.md §"Lark / Discord / …".

# =====================================================================
# RESERVED — alternate LLM dispatchers (planned)
# =====================================================================
# Spec V3 §33 declares Dispatcher as pluggable. V1 ships only claude-code.

# HERALD_OPENCODE_*
# HERALD_AIDER_*
# HERALD_GEMINI_API_KEY=
# HERALD_CURSOR_*
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=                # for Anthropic Managed Agent direct path

# =====================================================================
# Encryption at rest (optional; spec V3 §15.4)
# =====================================================================
# Only required if Herald itself encrypts credentials at rest (versus
# relying on the host's full-disk encryption).

# HERALD_DB_ENC_KEY=change-me-32-byte-hex-encoded-aes-key

# =====================================================================
# Operator audit notes (read OPERATOR_CREDENTIALS.md before editing)
# =====================================================================
# 1. NEVER copy this file's defaults to production.
# 2. Run the audit checklist (OPERATOR_CREDENTIALS.md §"Audit checklist")
#    BEFORE every commit. Any "BLOCK" output stops the commit.
# 3. Rotate any credential the moment it leaks to a remote — git history
#    scrubbing is forensic-quality, not retroactively invalidating.
